data.value:
Guidelines:
The objective is to achieve the highest score and eliminate the other rivals. Being the last one standing doesn't mean winning, the player with the highest score will be victorious.
Scoring:
Each time you pass a tile you will be given approximately 65 points,calling airstrikes will grant you 300 score, eliminating an opponent (either airstrike or WMD) will give you 1000 score and being the last one standing will grant you 2000 points.
Support Powers:
1)Surgical Strike: Costs 700 points and one turn, in return it deals 30% damage initially on a selected opponent. 2)Surgical strike upgrade: Costs 1800 points and three turns, in return it increases the surgical strike damage by 15%. 3)Field Repairs: Costs 300 points and one turn, in return it repairs the player 20% initially . 4)Field Repairs upgrade: Costs 1200 points and two turns, in return it increases the field repairs by 15%.
Special Tiles:
1)EMP blast: Causes the player who stops at it to be deprived from one turn. 2)Repairs: Increases the player's health when he stops at it by 40%. 3)WMD: Allows the player who stops at it to immediately kill an opponent.
Imperative Tactics:
1)Before finishing off the last opponent you must ensure that your score is higher than him. 2)Be careful using the support powers, while they are an essential tool to victory, they cost alot of points. 3)Depending on the situation, sometimes playing an economical game makes an easy win.
